cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with maximizing the long-term time-average throughput of a point-to-point link, which is a classic problem in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses a model for a point-to-point link between an energy harvesting transmitter and receiver, which is a common scenario in wireless networking. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes online policies for power control in an uncoordinated dual energy harvesting link, which can be seen as a control problem. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper deals with a distributed power control problem, which can be seen as a multiagent system. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper proposes a fully uncoordinated policy, which can be seen as a game-theoretic solution to the power control problem.
